then it's gonna actually do that 1,000

00:24:16.400 --> 00:24:20.479
and not dynamically adjust.

00:24:21.479 --> 00:24:25.319
It's going to not do the same type of dynamic adjusting

00:24:25.319 --> 00:24:28.560
it would if it wasn't fixed width equals true.

00:24:28.560 --> 00:24:30.079
You can play around with all these parameters.

00:24:30.079 --> 00:24:32.119
There's a lot of customization.

00:24:32.119 --> 00:24:34.520
I think oftentimes it's trickier to get into like,

00:24:34.520 --> 00:24:36.479
you know, these fixed width scenarios.

00:24:36.479 --> 00:24:39.359
I usually think it's better practice to just,

00:24:39.359 --> 00:24:42.239
you know, let things dynamically fill the space

00:24:42.239 --> 00:24:44.640
based on how much screen real estate you have.

00:24:44.640 --> 00:24:45.520
So I kind of like, you know,

00:24:45.520 --> 00:24:48.560
doing this width equals one half type approach.

00:24:48.560 --> 00:24:50.239
So I'm gonna go ahead and do that.

